Story makes us human.
Neural circuitry is designed to crave story.

Writers can change the way people think simply by giving them a glimpse of life through 
their characters eyes.

FOr a story to captivate a reader, it must continually meet his or her hardwired 
expectations.

each chapter ends with checklist you can apply to your work at any stage

you have to be honest about your story as you would be about a novel you pick up in a 
bookstore, or a movie youre about to watch.

pinpoint where each trouble spot lies and then remedy it before it spreads like a weed,
undermining your entire narrative.

its a lot more fun that it sounds because there's nothing more exhilarating than
watching your work improve until your readers are so engrossed in it that they forgot 
that it is story at all.